v0.2.4 (16 Mar 2013)
	Timeouts cleared on exit.

v0.2.3 (15 Mar 2013)
	Deleted new domain error properties in node v0.10.

v0.2.2 (09 Mar 2013)
	"redirectError()" can be used to redirect directly to the default error
		handler.

v0.2.1 (05 Mar 2013)
	Removed "next()" in "redirectError()".
	"dom(obj)" returns null if "obj" is not the request object.

v0.2.0 (04 Mar 2013)
	Full Express support.

v0.1.6 (02 Mar 2013)
	Specific request domains has been added.
	Added "errorHandler()".
	Modified "redirectError()" behaviour.
	Modified "dom()" behaviour.
	Added Express example and how to properly handle errors.

v0.1.5 (28 Feb 2013)
	When all the workers die the master emits a "shutdown" event.

v0.1.4 (28 Feb 2013)
	Renamed module to "grace".
	Added "redirectError()".

v0.1.3 (23 Feb 2013)
	Fixed workers check on master.

v0.1.2 (22 Feb 2013)
	Added "exit" event.

v0.1.1 (20 Feb 2013)
	Added exit code to "shutdown()".
	Fixed exit code when a worker dies due to an error in the start or shutdown
		listeners or a callback with error in the shutdown, now returns 1.
	Some bugfixes.
	
v0.1.0 (19 Feb 2013)
	Added "dom()".
	Removed domain properties from the emitted error objects.
	Workers now accept a timeout before killing them.
	Some bugfixes.

v0.0.4 (16 Feb 2013)
	Uncaught exceptions were killing the application.
	Exit timeout now kills correctly the master/worker (keep-alive was preventing
		to kill the worker).

v0.0.3 (16 Feb 2013)
	Prevent from calling "shutdown()" more than one time.
	Better support for workers.

v0.0.2 (15 Feb 2013)
	Added "timeout()".

v0.0.1 (14 Feb 2013)
	First commit.